Pre-Game Insights: Gambia are playing Comoros for the first time.
Comoros and Gambia will play at the Ben M'Hamed El Abdi Stadium in El Jadida, Morocco.
Comoros are ranked 119th in the world and are aiming to reach their second AFCON finals.
Comoros head coach Stefano Cusin has called up 24 players, including prolific attacker El Fardou Ben Nabouhane and Troyes striker Rafiki Said.
Gambia are looking to reach their third consecutive AFCON finals.
Gambia have named 24 players in their squad, including Musa Barrow and rising star Yankubah Minteh.
Miscellaneous Highlights: This is the first ever clash between Comoros and Gambia in all competitions.
Gambia have won just once in five official games this year, a 5-1 defeat of Seychelles in a 2026 FIFA World Cup qualifier.
Gambia's Yankubah Minteh is looking to score in his third consecutive game.
Comoros have won just thrice from nine games this year.
